[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pollution in atmosphere could cause intense weather

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new study claims that intense weather in some parts of the world might be caused by increased pollution in the atmosphere.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
10 March 2015 Last updated at 08:20 GMT
The American space agency Nasa has been monitoring special space satellites that show the affect different types of pollution can have.
They're worried that emissions from factories in China could be affecting weather in the US.
BBC Weather expert Sarah Keith-Lucas has more details.
